<html><head><title>Zatozia's Tips for Celebrating EQ's Anniversary</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Zatozia's Tips for Celebrating EQ's Anniversary</h3><p>Zatozia, EQ's Community Manager, has some tips on how to enjoy the 8th Anniversary events around Norrath:<br><br>Here are some ways you can celebrate: <br><br>Take part in the Anniversary Festivities!<br><br>In Game:<br>-We have introduced dozens of Fabled Luclin NPCs. -We brought back all the fabled fiends of years past. -There is a new scavenger hunt! Speak with Tyla Filinav in the Nexus if you are interested in helping her collect a few things. -These Anniversary Festivities will be available from March 16, 2007 through April 16, 2007. <br><br>Out of Game:<br>-Visit The Dungeon and The Harpy's Head Tavern section of the EverQuest Forums to write stories, share your screenshots of your parties, raids, and adventures. <br><br>Help your friends play!<br><br>-Help your friends try out new characters. Help them get up to speed with their old characters! Help them Party!<br>-Invite old friends to return to EverQuest for the weekend.<br>-Invite new friends to play for free<br><br>Visit your home city!<br>Throughout the year, you can get so busy that you forget about the city where you were born. Take time out this weekend to visit your home city. <br><br>Anniversary Hail!<br>Greet everyone you meet in game with a Happy 8th Anniversary greeting. <br><br>Party!<br>Make use of the taverns and inns across the world by throwing a big party for your friends and be sure to invite others. Perhaps even in The Arena where you can have a little bit extra fun with the party! </div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Monday, 19 Mar, 2007<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=27586">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=27586</a><br>Printed On: Sat Mar 24 0:14:22 PDT 2007<br>©2005 IGN Entertainment</font></span>